    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>Faelan fixes his unblinking eyes on you for a moment, stopping you in your tracks, then quickly looks away. You take a moment to recollect your thoughts.</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts>
        <string>aod.npc_faelan_met = true;</string>
        <string>Addjournalchar(faelan);</string>
      </onLoadScripts>
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“How do you do it?”</text>
          <def_link>1</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>0</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“I just do,” says Faelan, his voice grating and harsh. “Brother Meru says that I’m touched by the Gods. I used to think I was cursed. Now I’m not sure.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Why?”</text>
          <def_link>2</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>1</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“It brought me nothing but pain. I was beaten half to death more times than I can remember. I drifted between the worlds for days at a time and that’s when my gift grew stronger.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“You drifted between the worlds?”</text>
          <def_link>3</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>2</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“That’s what my brother told me. He was looking after me until a sickness took him. I slept for days, neither dead nor alive. No healer could wake me up, yet my brother never gave up. He dripped sugary water into my mouth and waited until I wake up.

“He begged me to keep my eyes down but I just couldn’t. The thrill, the excitement, the power ... it was all too much for me. How was I supposed to know that I was being tested by the Gods?”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“So now you serve Brother Meru?”</text>
          <def_link>4</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>3</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“He saved me from the gallows and gave me purpose. When I took my first life, the pain was excruciating. I was within those men when they died. Or maybe I was all these men and died one body at a time until only my own was still breathing? There are many living things that kill yet what killer gets to experience his victims’ suffering and live through it?”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Did you kill again?”</text>
          <def_link>5</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>4</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“I did,” says Faelan, showing no emotions. “Brother Meru convinced me that the gift was given to me for a reason. It would be an affront to the Gods to reject their gift.

“Sharing the agonies and dying over and over again are my penance and absolution. I think he’s right. The pain is indiscernible yet I find that I miss it when I go too long without punishing the human wickedness.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Pain or pleasure?”</text>
          <def_link>6</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Does your power grow still?”</text>
          <def_link>9</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick>
            <string>aod.streetwise &gt;= 6</string>
          </checksOnClick>
          <linksOnClick>
            <int>10</int>
          </linksOnClick>
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Do you share Brother Meru’s beliefs?”</text>
          <def_link>7</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>5</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“Extreme pain is indistinguishable from extreme pleasure. They are two different paths to the same destination, I think.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Does your power grow still?”</text>
          <def_link>9</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick>
            <string>aod.streetwise &gt;= 6</string>
          </checksOnClick>
          <linksOnClick>
            <int>10</int>
          </linksOnClick>
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Do you share Brother Meru’s beliefs?”</text>
          <def_link>7</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>Leave.</text>
          <def_link>8</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>6</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“I want to feel what Brother Meru does,” says Faelan, “but I can’t. It too is denied to me.” For a moment there he sounds angry but then he closes his eyes, his lips move, either praying or counting. When he opens his eyes, you can read nothing in them.

“I must have faith. The Gods have a plan for me.”</npc_text>
